<body>

  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-main">
      <h1>Soothing Herbal Cough &amp; Mucus Tea</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A warm, gentle tea designed to soothe throat irritation, calm cough,
        and help thin mucus associated with post-nasal drip.
      </p>

      <div class="recipe-meta">
        <span class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Beverages</span>
        <span class="badge">Stovetop</span>
        <span class="badge">~10 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <nav class="link-row" aria-label="Primary">
    <a href="./">All Recipes</a>
    <a href="#" aria-current="page">Soothing Herbal Cough &amp; Mucus Tea</a>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" onclick="window.print()">Print</button>
  </nav>

  <main class="layout">

    <aside class="sidebar card" aria-label="Recipe navigation">
      <div class="sidebar-title">Browse</div>
      <div class="sidebar-search">
        <input
          id="recipeSearch"
          type="text"
          placeholder="Search recipes…"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
      </div>
      <div id="sidebarContent" class="text-muted">Loading…</div>
    </aside>

    <section>

      <!-- Ingredients -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <div>
            <div class="card-title">Ingredients</div>
            <div class="card-subtitle">For one soothing cup</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ingredients">
          <ul>
            <li>1 cup hot water (warm, not boiling)</li>
            <li>½–1 teaspoon fresh ginger, grated</li>
            <li>¼ teaspoon ground turmeric</li>
            <li>1–2 teaspoons honey, to taste</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice</li>
            <li>Optional: pinch of black pepper</li>
            <li>Optional: 1 peppermint, sage, or chamomile tea bag</li>
            <li>Optional: 2–3 fresh thyme sprigs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Procedure -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <div>
            <div class="card-title">Procedure</div>
            <div class="card-subtitle">Steep and sip</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="procedure">
          <ol>
            <li>Heat water until hot but not boiling.</li>
            <li>Add grated ginger and turmeric to a mug.</li>
            <li>Pour hot water over the mixture and steep for 5 minutes.</li>
            <li>Add honey and lemon juice and stir until dissolved.</li>
            <li>Add optional tea bag or herbs and steep an additional 3–5 minutes.</li>
            <li>Strain if desired and sip slowly while warm.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <hr class="soft" />

        <div class="card-info-box">
          <strong>Notes:</strong>
          This tea is intended as a gentle, supportive remedy for throat irritation
          and cough caused by post-nasal drip.
          Warm fluids help thin mucus, while honey coats the throat and ginger
          provides mild anti-inflammatory benefits.
          <br /><br />
